Here's a simple example of a recursion function in Python. The function calculates the factorial of a number. Each recursive call to the function is passed a smaller version of the input, the base case being a value of 1.
```python
def factorial(n):
    return 1 if n == 1 else n * factorial(n-1)
```
This simple, recursive solution is an excellent pedagogical tool. The function's behavior is mathematically equivalent to the iterative approach, but it directly visualizes the structure of the computation. This provides more insight into how recursive algorithms work.
